      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-4">Typical specifications from Hytrol, Interroll, Dematic, and Intelligrated product lines. See <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">conveyor cost guide</a> for pricing details.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Decision Guide -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="decision-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Decision Guide</div>
      <h2 id="decision-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Which Live Roller Technology <span class="text-accent">Do You Need?</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Start with Product Weight</h3>
        <p>Product weight is the first and most decisive filter. Products under 250 lbs qualify for any live roller technology including MDR. Products from 250-500 lbs narrow the field to BDLR. Products over 500 lbs require <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a>.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Do You Need Accumulation?</h3>
        <p>If yes, <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR</a> provides the simplest and most reliable <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">zero-pressure accumulation</a>. BDLR with pneumatic zones is the traditional alternative. Line-shaft provides light passive accumulation through O-ring slip. CDLR does not accumulate (continuous positive drive).</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Is Noise a Constraint?</h3>
        <p>MDR operates at 55-65 dB , conversational level. BDLR runs at 70-80 dB. Line-shaft and CDLR run at 75-85 dB. Facilities with hundreds of feet of conveyor in occupied work areas benefit significantly from MDR's quiet operation.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Do You Need Diverting?</h3>
        <p>Line-shaft conveyors work best with pop-up <a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">transfer</a> diverters because individual rollers can be disengaged from the shaft at the transfer point without affecting the rest of the conveyor. BDLR and MDR also work with transfers but require different zone control approaches at the divert point.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Budget: Upfront vs Total Cost</h3>
        <p>BDLR and line-shaft cost less per foot upfront ($$). MDR and CDLR cost more ($$$). However, MDR's on-demand energy use (zones only power when product is present) and lower maintenance (no belts, chains, or O-rings to replace) typically deliver a lower total cost of ownership over the conveyor's 15-20 year lifespan. The <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">conveyor cost guide</a> breaks down these factors.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Mixed Systems</h3>
        <p>Most <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">automated conveyor systems</a> combine multiple live roller technologies. A typical <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging line</a> might use MDR for accumulation zones, BDLR for high-speed transport sections, CDLR for pallet handling, and <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">gravity roller</a> for take-away and manual stations. The conveyor frame and roller dimensions can be matched across technologies for seamless product transition between sections.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
